This paper is about developing cross-lingual systems for question answering, which involves natural language processing and machine learning. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). Additionally, the paper discusses the use of state-of-the-art cross-lingual representations and machine translation, which are relevant to sub-categories such as cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also involves information retrieval techniques, which could place it in the cs.IR (Information Retrieval) sub-category. Finally, the paper discusses the use of multilingual evaluation benchmarks, which could be relevant to the cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) sub-category.
